#: ../../language/docs.md:1
msgid "Comments and Documentation"
msgstr "注释与文档"

#: ../../language/docs.md:3
msgid "Comments"
msgstr "注释"

#: ../../language/docs.md:5
msgid "Use `//` for ordinary comments inside code:"
msgstr "在代码内部使用 `//` 编写普通注释："

#: ../../language/docs.md:7
msgid ""
"// Explain why this branch exists.\n"
"let retries = 3\n"
msgstr ""
"// Explain why this branch exists.\n"
"let retries = 3\n"

#: ../../language/docs.md:12
msgid ""
"You will also often see `///|` at the start of top-level blocks. It is an"
" empty doc-comment line used to split top-level items explicitly. This "
"matters for documentation tooling today, and it also preserves clear top-"
"level block boundaries for future caching and other tooling purposes. In "
"practice, `///|` is useful in ordinary MoonBit code as well as in "
"documentation sources."
msgstr ""
"你也会经常在顶层代码块开头看到 "
"`///|`。它是一条空的文档注释行，用来显式分隔顶层条目。这对于当前的文档工具链很重要，也能为未来的缓存和其他工具用途保留清晰的顶层块边界。实际使用中，`///|`"
" 不仅适用于文档源码，在普通的 MoonBit 代码里也很有用。"

#: ../../language/docs.md:18
msgid "Doc Comments"
msgstr "文档注释"

#: ../../language/docs.md:20
msgid ""
"Doc comments use `///` on each line immediately before a top-level item "
"such as `fn`, `let`, `enum`, `struct`, or `type`. Doc comments are "
"written in Markdown."
msgstr ""
"文档注释使用 `///`，逐行写在 `fn`、`let`、`enum`、`struct`、`type` 等顶层条目前面。文档注释内容使用 "
"Markdown 编写。"

#: ../../language/docs.md:24
msgid ""
"/// Return a new array with reversed elements.\n"
"fn[T] reverse(xs : Array[T]) -> Array[T] {\n"
"  ...\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"/// 返回一个新数组，其中元素被反转。\n"
"fn[T] reverse(xs : Array[T]) -> Array[T] {\n"
"  ...\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../language/docs.md:31
msgid ""
"Markdown code blocks inside doc comments marked with `mbt check` are "
"treated as document tests. `moon check` and `moon test` will "
"automatically check and run these tests, so that examples in doc comments"
" are always up-to-date. Wrap the snippet in `test { .. }` when you want a"
" test block:"
msgstr ""
"文档注释中的 Markdown 代码块如果标记为 `mbt check`，就会被视作文档测试；`moon check` 和 `moon test`"
" 会自动检查并运行这些测试，从而保证文档注释中的示例始终是最新的。需要测试块时，请将代码包在 `test { .. }` 中："

#: ../../language/docs.md:36
msgid ""
"/// Increment an integer by one,\n"
"///\n"
"/// Example:\n"
"/// ```mbt check\n"
"/// test {\n"
"///   inspect(incr(41), content=\"42\")\n"
"/// }\n"
"/// ```\n"
"pub fn incr(x : Int) -> Int {\n"
"  x + 1\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"/// 将一个整数加一，\n"
"///\n"
"/// 示例：\n"
"/// ```mbt check\n"
"/// test {\n"
"///   inspect(incr(41), content=\"42\")\n"
"/// }\n"
"/// ```\n"
"pub fn incr(x : Int) -> Int {\n"
"  x + 1\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../language/docs.md:42
msgid ""
"If you want to prevent a code snippet from being treated as a document "
"test, mark it with a language id other than `mbt check` on the markdown "
"code block:"
msgstr "如果想要阻止一段代码被当作文档测试，只需要在它的 markdown 代码块上标记一个 `mbt check` 以外的语言名字："

#: ../../language/docs.md:45
msgid ""
"/// `c_incr(x)` is the same as the following C code:\n"
"/// ```c\n"
"/// x++\n"
"/// ```\n"
"pub fn c_incr(x : Ref[Int]) -> Int {\n"
"  let old = x.val\n"
"  x.val += 1\n"
"  old\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"/// `c_incr(x)` 等价于下面的 C 代码：\n"
"/// ```c\n"
"/// x++\n"
"/// ```\n"
"pub fn c_incr(x : Ref[Int]) -> Int {\n"
"  let old = x.val\n"
"  x.val += 1\n"
"  old\n"
"}\n"

#: ../../language/docs.md:51
msgid ""
"Currently, document tests are always [blackbox tests](/language/tests.md"
"#blackbox-tests-and-whitebox-tests). So private definitions cannot have "
"document test."
msgstr ""
"目前，文档测试都是 [黑盒测试](/language/tests.md#blackbox-tests-and-whitebox-"
"tests)。所以私有定义目前不能有文档测试。"

#: ../../language/docs.md:54
msgid "Literate `.mbt.md` Files"
msgstr "文学化 `.mbt.md` 文件"

#: ../../language/docs.md:56
msgid ""
"MoonBit also supports literate Markdown files ending in `.mbt.md`. These "
"files can live inside a package as checked documentation, or they can be "
"used as standalone single-file inputs to `moon check` and `moon test`."
msgstr ""
"MoonBit 也支持以 `.mbt.md` 结尾的文学化 Markdown 文件。这些文件既可以作为包内的可检查文档，也可以作为 `moon "
"check` 和 `moon test` 的独立单文件输入。"

#: ../../language/docs.md:60
msgid "For a standalone file, run:"
msgstr "对于独立文件，运行："

#: ../../language/docs.md:62
msgid ""
"moon check README.mbt.md\n"
"moon test README.mbt.md\n"
msgstr ""
"moon check README.mbt.md\n"
"moon test README.mbt.md\n"

#: ../../language/docs.md:67
msgid ""
"Inside a project, keep using the package-level `moon check` and `moon "
"test` commands instead."
msgstr "在项目内部，请继续使用包级别的 `moon check` 和 `moon test` 命令。"

#: ../../language/docs.md:70
msgid "The code fence language controls how each block is handled:"
msgstr "代码块的语言标记决定了每个代码块会如何处理："

#: ../../language/docs.md:72
msgid "`mbt`: MoonBit code that is compiled, but does not create a test entry."
msgstr "`mbt`：会编译其中的 MoonBit 代码，但不会创建测试入口。"

#: ../../language/docs.md:73
msgid ""
"`mbt check`: MoonBit document-test code. Use `test { .. }` or `async "
"test` inside the block when you want assertions."
msgstr "`mbt check`：MoonBit 文档测试代码。需要断言时，请在代码块内部使用 `test { .. }` 或 `async test`。"

#: ../../language/docs.md:75
msgid "`mbt nocheck`: Show MoonBit code without compiling or testing it."
msgstr "`mbt nocheck`：展示 MoonBit 代码，但不编译也不测试。"

#: ../../language/docs.md:76
msgid ""
"`moonbit`: Ordinary displayed code block for documentation; it is not "
"compiled or tested."
msgstr "`moonbit`：普通的文档展示代码块，不会被编译或测试。"

#: ../../language/docs.md:79
msgid "For example:"
msgstr "例如："

#: ../../language/docs.md:81
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"```mbt nocheck\n"
"///|\n"
"fn helper() -> Int {\n"
"  42\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
"\n"
"```mbt check\n"
"///|\n"
"test \"forty two\" {\n"
"  inspect(40 + 2, content=\"42\")\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
"\n"
"```mbt nocheck\n"
"///|\n"
"fn native_only() -> Unit {\n"
"  ...\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""
"```mbt\n"
"///|\n"
"fn helper() -> Int {\n"
"  42\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
"\n"
"```mbt check\n"
"///|\n"
"test \"helper\" {\n"
"  inspect(helper(), content=\"42\")\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
"\n"
"```mbt nocheck\n"
"// Pseudocode or platform-specific code that should not be checked.\n"
"```\n"

#: ../../language/docs.md:87
msgid ""
"Standalone `.mbt.md` files can also declare front matter to specify "
"imports or the target backend:"
msgstr "独立的 `.mbt.md` 文件也可以声明 front matter 来指定导入或目标后端："

#: ../../language/docs.md:90
msgid ""
"---\n"
"moonbit:\n"
"  import:\n"
"    - path: moonbitlang/core/ref\n"
"      alias: ref\n"
"  backend:\n"
"    native\n"
"---\n"
"\n"
"```mbt check\n"
"fn answer() -> Int {\n"
"  let cell : @ref.Ref[Int] = { val: 41 }\n"
"  cell.val + 1\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"///|\n"
"test \"answer\" {\n"
"  inspect(answer(), content=\"42\")\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/docs.md:94
msgid ""
"Use `moonbit.import` when you want to name the packages the file can "
"import directly. Use `moonbit.deps` when you only want to declare module "
"dependencies and let Moon synthesize the imports automatically."
msgstr ""
"当你想显式指定该文件可以直接导入哪些包时，使用 `moonbit.import`。当你只想声明模块依赖并让 Moon 自动合成导入时，使用 "
"`moonbit.deps`。"
